OL,3,CRogue builders exposed by voice note
OL,4,Cin #37K roof scam
OL,6,FThe fraud began when two men `
OL,7,Fincluding Lee ` knocked on the
OL,8,Fvictim's door, claiming urgent roof
OL,9,Frepairs were needed.
OL,11,FThey handed him a leaflet for 'Roofing
OL,12,FRepair Specialists' and verbally
OL,13,Fquoted #12,000 for repairs, plus
OL,14,F#2,000 for scaffolding and another
OL,15,F#2,000 to remove a nearby tree.
OL,17,FThey demanded #3,000 upfront to buy
OL,18,Fmaterials.
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G3/8
